vulnerability.name: USN-6367-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that Firefox did not properly manage memory when handling WebP images. If a user were tricked into opening a webpage containing malicious WebP image file, an attacker could potentially exploit these to cause a denial of service or execute arbitrary code. (CVE-2023-4863)

statements.status_notes: Firefox could be made to crash or run programs if it opened a malicious website.
